
Overview of noun lotus

The noun lotus has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) lotus, Indian lotus, sacred lotus, Nelumbo nucifera -- (native to eastern Asia; widely cultivated for its large pink or white flowers)
2. Lotus, genus Lotus -- (annual or perennial herbs or subshrubs)
3. lotus, white lotus, Egyptian water lily, white lily, Nymphaea lotus -- (white Egyptian lotus: water lily of Egypt to southeastern Africa; held sacred by the Egyptians)
